name: Female Orangutan (Pongo pygmaeus) #1
description: Orangutans are great apes native to the rainforests of Indonesia and Malaysia. They are found only in parts of Borneo and Sumatra and the name orangutan means "man of the forest" in the Malay language. In the lowland forests in which they reside, orangutans live solitary existences. Orangutans are "gardeners" of the forest, playing a vital role in seed dispersal in their habitats. They live in tropical forests and prefer forest in river valleys and floodplains of their respective islands. The first series of orangutan aim to will help them for extinction.
